title: Google\Cloud\AutoMl\V1\ModelEvaluation
name: ModelEvaluation
description:
Evaluation results of a model.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.automl.v1.ModelEvaluation

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.classification_evaluation_metrics
params.description: Model evaluation metrics for image, text, video and tables classification. Tables problem is considered a classification when the target column is CATEGORY DataType.

params.name: data.translation_evaluation_metrics
params.description: Model evaluation metrics for translation.

params.name: data.image_object_detection_evaluation_metrics
params.description: Model evaluation metrics for image object detection.

params.name: data.text_sentiment_evaluation_metrics
params.description: Evaluation metrics for text sentiment models.

params.name: data.text_extraction_evaluation_metrics
params.description: Evaluation metrics for text extraction models.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. Resource name of the model evaluation. Format: projects/{project_id}/locations/{location_id}/models/{model_id}/modelEvaluations/{model_evaluation_id}

params.name: data.annotation_spec_id
params.description: Output only. The ID of the annotation spec that the model evaluation applies to. The The ID is empty for the overall model evaluation. For Tables annotation specs in the dataset do not exist and this ID is always not set, but for CLASSIFICATION [prediction_type-s][google.cloud.automl.v1.TablesModelMetadata.prediction_type] the [display_name][google.cloud.automl.v1.ModelEvaluation.display_name] field is used.

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: Output only. The value of [display_name][google.cloud.automl.v1.AnnotationSpec.display_name] at the moment when the model was trained. Because this field returns a value at model training time, for different models trained from the same dataset, the values may differ, since display names could had been changed between the two model's trainings. For Tables CLASSIFICATION [prediction_type-s][google.cloud.automl.v1.TablesModelMetadata.prediction_type] distinct values of the target column at the moment of the model evaluation are populated here. The display_name is empty for the overall model evaluation.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Output only. Timestamp when this model evaluation was created.

params.name: data.evaluated_example_count
params.description: Output only. The number of examples used for model evaluation, i.e. for which ground truth from time of model creation is compared against the predicted annotations created by the model. For overall ModelEvaluation (i.e. with annotation_spec_id not set) this is the total number of all examples used for evaluation. Otherwise, this is the count of examples that according to the ground truth were annotated by the [annotation_spec_id][google.cloud.automl.v1.ModelEvaluation.annotation_spec_id].
